{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05deb0b8-e619-4a82-91ed-77d5c050215b","content":"The directory is empty, so I'll answer based on the Copilot skill-validator evaluation framework.\n\n## Evaluation Format\n\nEvaluations are defined in an **`evaluation.yml`** file using this structure:\n\n```yaml\nquestions:\n  - question: \"What products are available under $50?\"\n    expectations:\n      - The response lists only products priced below $50\n      - The response includes product names and prices\n    difficulty: basic\n\n  - question: \"Compare the top-rated laptop and tablet by specs and price\"\n    expectations:\n      - The response calls tools to retrieve both laptop and tablet data\n      - The response compares specifications side-by-side\n    difficulty: advanced\n```\n\nEach question has a **natural-language prompt**, a list of **expectations** (graded independently), and a **difficulty** level.\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n1. **Cover all tools** — at least one question per tool in your MCP server\n2. **Vary difficulty** — include `basic` (single tool call), `advanced` (multi-step/multi-tool), and edge cases\n3. **Test realistic intent** — phrase questions the way a real user would, not like API docs\n4. **Expectations should be observable** — assert on output content (e.g., \"includes price\"), not internal reasoning\n5. **Include negative cases** — e.g., \"Find products in category 'xyz'\" where none exist, to test graceful handling\n6. **Avoid ambiguity** — each expectation should be clearly pass/fail\n\n### Example questions for a product catalog:\n\n| Type | Example |\n|---|---|\n| Single tool | *\"List all products in the 'Electronics' category\"* |\n| Filtering | *\"Which products cost between $20 and $50?\"* |\n| Multi-tool | *\"Find the cheapest product and check if it's in stock\"* |\n| Edge case | *\"Search for products matching 'xyznonexistent'\"* |\n| Reasoning | *\"Which category has the highest average rating?\"* |\n\nStart with 5–10 questions covering your core tool surface, then expand to edge cases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1fc64b55-bc06-47c6-bb2c-d27f897939b1","outputTokens":491,"requestId":"F042:A8FAA:269E43F:2AB3846:69F9407F"},"id":"63119996-fbb2-40d5-b864-594c8a3d9c5f","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:57:49.646Z","parentId":"dbf7b779-4e73-44b4-b4d1-f43e235a1e57"}
